Req. ID: 292001 
As a Principal Product Engineer Lead, you will lead a team of engineers responsible for characterization, optimization, and pathfinding of emerging memory technology array including cell, sense amp, and access device. You will be driving the strategic direction of next generation memory technology! 
Responsibilities and Tasks include the following, but not limited to: 
Develop, mentor, and drive a group of product engineers of varying experience 
Champion the characterization around key components of the memory cell intrinsic performance 
Build, maintain, and improve testing and characterization methods, future circuits, and data analysis methodologies 
Collaborate with Design, Process Integration, and Cell Engineers to streamline the cell improvement effort (Read-window, performance, reliability), analyzing data, and providing direction for process and cell experiments 
Apply cell device physics knowledge to array and sense amp operation to both help set metrics for performance and reliability requirements and enable new technologies to achieve these requirements 
Help orchestrate array failure mode and effect analysis (FMEA) efforts, mentoring engineers in hands-on electrical failure analysis (EFA), and driving multi-functional teams to address device and array deficiencies 
Lead team to analyze array performance and support process qualification of emerging memory technologies to enable new product development and manufacturability. 
Set strategy for future emerging memory array. 
Present data in a clear and concise format updating management and multi-functional teams 
Qualifications: 
Bachelor or Master Degree in Physics, Material Science, Electrical, Computer, or other fields of Engineering 
Experience in semiconductor product, design, or process engineering with 10+ or more yearsâ€™ experience. 
Excellent verbal and written communication skills 
Strong problem-solving and analytical skills 
Significant Experience with VLSI, Cadence, CMOS process, and through knowledge of Semiconductor Device Physics 
Advanced memory (DRAM, SRAM, NAND, NOR, or 3DXP) knowledge 
Proven track record to lead successful projects while mentoring, coaching, and effectively developing other specialists 
Prior experience as Lead or Supervisor is a plus but not required 
Appetite for learning and collaborating in a team environment! 
